snippet.textDisplay:
Just a tip for next time, the reason you were blowing breakers and having extension lead troubles is that because the resistance of the power feed goes up heaps with longer extension leads, more resistance = higher Amp draw (V = I x R)

Next time buy some 15A extension leads but grind down the Earth pin so that they still fit in the regular socket, shouldn’t have any more issues 👍🏻
snippet.textOriginal:
